title: Jeff Phelps Oral History Interview for the Georgia Dental Project
description: Jeff Phelps, a 1973 Grinnell College graduate, discusses his involvement in the college's concert program, particularly as North Lounge coordinator. He highlights Georgia's crucial role in organizing concerts, including securing bands like The Jackson Five and Jefferson Airplane. He shares personal anecdotes about the community's reaction to concerts and the impact of Georgia's booking skills. Jeff emphasizes Georgia's influence on his love for live music and her significant contributions to the college's cultural scene.

title: James Kissane '52 History Interview for the Georgia Dental Project
description: Dr. James Kissane '52 is an alumnus of Grinnell College and former Professor in the Grinnell College English Department from 1956 into the early 2000s. This interview discusses his time on the Public Events Committee alongside Georgia Dentel, the impact of classical music and orchestras on campus culture, and reflections on college life in the late 1940s and early 1950s in relation to the GI Bill, gender, and academics.
